headline: Earnings, Fed talk, mortgage rates, jobless claims: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton explains the biggest market stories on Thursday, July 10. Delta (DAL) and ConAgra (CAG) will report their earnings in the morning, and Levi's (LEVI) is reporting earnings after the closing bell. Fresh Fed commentary will be out, as St. Louis Fed President Alberto Musalem and San Francisco Fed President Mary Daly are both set to be delivering remarks. Freddie Mac (FMCC) is publishing weekly mortgage rate data for the week of July 3. Initial jobless claims data for the week ending July 5 will be posted. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here.

headline: Conagra Brands Announces Quarterly Dividend Payment
summary: Conagra Brands, Inc. (NYSE: CAG) today announced that its Board of Directors approved a quarterly dividend payment of $0.35 per share of CAG common stock to be paid on August 28, 2025 to stockholders of record as of the close of business on July 30, 2025. Conagra Brands, Inc. has paid consecutive quarterly dividends since January 1976.

headline: 2 Ultra-High-Yield Dividend Stocks at 10-Year Lows to Buy in July
summary: The packaged food industry is facing its largest downturn in over a decade.  Conagra Brands and Campbell's have become too cheap to ignore.  Packaged food giants Conagra Brands (NYSE: CAG) and The Campbell's Company (NASDAQ: CPB) are both down more than 25% year to date and are hovering around their lowest levels in over a decade.
